The suit does not have insulating properties, which is why I did not implement the 0K aspect. In regards to keeping him in a vacuum, that would also have caused issues due to the pressure of anti air within his suit - in a vacuum the suit would have expanded drastically, and may have been at risk of bursting. Likewise, at the time when the containment procedures were in effect, it would have caused -1 severe discomfort, which is the opposite of what the Foundation's intentions were at the time.

Nonetheless, the mentioned containment procedures are no longer used, as shown with the note shown in the collapsible name (when opened). He is now kept within his own specially-made room. I will be updating that the room is a notable distance from Area-32 though. Do you have any suggestions for a reasonable distance to place it at?







